<package name="ruby2.6" project="Virtualization:vagrant">
  <title>An Interpreted Object-Oriented Scripting Language</title>
  <description>Ruby is an interpreted scripting language for quick and easy
object-oriented programming.  It has many features for processing text
files and performing system management tasks (as in Perl).  It is
simple, straight-forward, and extensible.

* Ruby features:

- Simple Syntax

- *Normal* Object-Oriented features (class, method calls, for
   example)

- *Advanced* Object-Oriented features(Mix-in, Singleton-method, for
   example)

- Operator Overloading

- Exception Handling

- Iterators and Closures

- Garbage Collection

- Dynamic Loading of Object Files (on some architectures)

- Highly Portable (works on many UNIX machines; DOS, Windows, Mac,
BeOS, and more)

</description>
  <build>
    <disable repository="SLE_11_SP4"/>
    <disable/>
    <enable repository="SLE_12_SP1"/>
    <enable repository="SLE_12_SP2"/>
    <enable repository="SLE_12_SP3"/>
    <enable repository="SLE_12_SP4"/>
    <enable repository="SLE_15-SP1"/>
  </build>
  <publish>
    <enable repository="openSUSE_Tumbleweed_and_d_l_r_e"/>
    <enable repository="openSUSE_Tumbleweed_default_ruby"/>
  </publish>
</package>
